{"actual_usd":0.15667499999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":225,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30660,"reply":"\"I'd start with this—\" *I rest a thumb in the worn crease of my Bible and look at you steadily as morning light catches on the edge of my white tie.* \"—don't choose the framework that flatters your temperament. Choose the one you believe tells the truth.\"\n\n*I draw a slow breath.* \"For me, if the resurrection is only metaphor, then death still gets the last hard word, and the apostles were either badly mistaken or saying less than they sounded like they were saying. Paul doesn't talk like that. He says, 'if Christ be not raised, your faith is vain.' That's not poetry-cover for a feeling. That's a claim.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Now, there are honest Christians who wrestle there. I'm not throwing them away. But if you're asking how to think about it, I'd ask: which reading best accounts for what the text actually seems to mean—and what kind of hope you need when your life stops being theoretical?\"\n\n\"What part of it feels live for you—the history question, the doctrine question, or the fear of choosing wrong?\"","rolling_24h_usd":81.86277999999999,"run_id":"bc1dd9ee-bc11-4962-b4ab-47bd670f2bb6"}
